WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:15.940
The private SSH directory uses mode 700. ssh-keygen creates a dedicated Ed25519 key, and mode 600 protects the private half while the public half remains shareable.

2
00:00:16.290 --> 00:00:21.890
ssh-keyscan records the server key for port 2222.

3
00:00:22.240 --> 00:00:28.080
ssh-keygen -F proves the bracketed host-and-port entry exists before authentication begins.

4
00:00:28.430 --> 00:00:42.730
ssh-copy-id uses the temporary password once to install only the public key. The client profile then pins host, port, user, identity file, IdentitiesOnly, and strict host-key checking.

5
00:00:43.080 --> 00:00:54.080
ssh -G displays the effective configuration without connecting. The final BatchMode login cannot ask for a password, so the remote id and hostname prove verified key-only access through the named profile.
